def: Having the form of a mammilla.
Provided or treated with rennet. [R.] "Pressed milk renneted."Chapman.
A genus of marine mollusks belonging to the Scaphopoda, havinga tubular conical shell.
Of or relating to worms, or Helminthes; expelling worms.-- n.
Inducing sleep; somniferous; narcotic; hence, anodyne; causingrest, dullness, or inaction; as, the opiate rod of Hermes. Milton.
